<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<%- include('../partials/head', { title: 'CollectIn Premium — AI-Powered LinkedIn Saved Posts Organization' ,
  description: 'Unlock premium features for CollectIn: AI categorization and advanced filtering for your LinkedIn saved posts collections.'
  , baseUrl: baseUrl, pageType: 'index' }) %>

  <body>
    <%- include('../partials/header', { isHome: false, baseUrl: baseUrl, title: title }) %>

      <main>
        <section id="premium" class="features-help">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
              <h2>Categorize with AI</h2>
              <p>Have hundreds of saved posts? Let AI categorize them for you.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-help-grid">
              <div class="feature-help">
                <h3>1. Scan step</h3>
                <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
                  <source src="assets/premium-scan.webm" type="video/mp4">
                  <track kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English captions" default>
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
                <p>CollectIn must find all your saved posts to categorize them. Start the scan and the extension will
                  scroll down automaticaly to find every post. Please stay on the page while the scan is running.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature-help">
                <h3>2. Categorize step</h3>
                <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
                  <source src="assets/premium-categorize.webm" type="video/mp4">
                  <track kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English captions" default>
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
                <p>With your posts scanned, CollectIn will do the hard workd to categorize them for you. It may time a
                  minute or two to complete, so please be patient.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature-help">
                <h3>3. Adjust categories</h3>
                <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
                  <source src="assets/premium-update-categories.webm" type="video/mp4">
                  <track kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English captions" default>
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
                <p>Not happy with the categories? No problem. You can adjust them to your liking. Hold the name of the
                  category to edit it. Move posts between categories by dragging and dropping (coming soon).</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature-help">
                <h3>4. Save and enjoy</h3>
                <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
                  <source src="assets/premium-save.webm" type="video/mp4">
                  <track kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English captions" default>
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
                <p>That's it! You can now enjoy your organized posts. Click on the "Apply categorization and reload
                  page" to see your posts organized in the new categories.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>

            <div class="section-header">
              <h2>Advanced filtering</h2>
              <p>Filter by author and date in a Side panel interface. This allows a more fluid and intuitive experience
                than the current LinkedIn's saved posts page with extra features.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-help-grid">
              <div class="feature-help">
                <h3>Coming Soon</h3>
                <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
                  <source src="assets/advanced-filtering.webm" type="video/mp4">
                  <track kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English captions" default>
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
              </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="cta">
          <div class="container cta-box">
            <h2>Upgrade to Premium</h2>
            <p>Unlock AI-powered categorization and advanced filtering for your LinkedIn collections.</p>
            <a class="button primary large" href="https://www.linkedin.com/my-items/saved-posts/?savedPostType=ALL"
              target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open
              saved posts page and click on the <span class="icon-magic">🪄</span> icon.</a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
  </body>

</html>